docs.abstract: A group of large hospital systems plans to create a nonprofit generic drug company to battle shortages and high prices.
docs.snippet: A group of large hospital systems plans to create a nonprofit generic drug company to battle shortages and high prices.
docs.lead_paragraph: For years, hospital executives have expressed frustration when essential drugs like heart medicines have become scarce, or when prices have skyrocketed because investors manipulated the market.

headline.main: Fed Up With Drug Companies, Hospitals Decide to Start Their Own
headline.print_headline: Fed Up With Drug Companies, Hospitals to Start Their Own

byline.original: By Reed Abelson and Katie Thomas

docs.abstract: Branded “idiots,” residents of Grimsby, England, choose romance for a dying fishing industry over another that is thriving.
docs.snippet: Branded “idiots,” residents of Grimsby, England, choose romance for a dying fishing industry over another that is thriving.
docs.lead_paragraph: GRIMSBY, England — There aren’t a lot of fishermen left in this town in North East England, once home to one of the largest fleet of trawlers in Britain. But nostalgia for the fishing industry permeates the place. So the result seemed inevitable when 70 percent of residents voted to leave the European Union. Britain’s fishermen have complained for years about regulations imposed on all members.

headline.main: In Brexit Vote, Town’s Nostalgia for Seafaring Past Muddied Its Future
headline.print_headline: Choosing Brexit, a Town Yearned for Its Seafaring Past, and Muddied Its Future

docs.abstract: Petrochemical companies were hit by a series of cyberassaults last year. The worst of them, against a widely used safety system, could have set off an explosion.
docs.snippet: Petrochemical companies were hit by a series of cyberassaults last year. The worst of them, against a widely used safety system, could have set off an explosion.
docs.lead_paragraph: In August, a petrochemical company with a plant in Saudi Arabia was hit by a new kind of cyberassault. The attack was not designed to simply destroy data or shut down the plant, investigators believe. It was meant to sabotage the firm’s operations and trigger an explosion.

headline.main: A Cyberattack in Saudi Arabia Had a Deadly Goal. Experts Fear Another Try.

byline.original: By Nicole Perlroth and Clifford Krauss

docs.abstract: A deepwater exploration agreement with the state-run oil company Rosneft was once one of Exxon’s most promising agreements.
docs.snippet: A deepwater exploration agreement with the state-run oil company Rosneft was once one of Exxon’s most promising agreements.
docs.lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — Exxon Mobil is abandoning its joint exploration ventures with the Russian oil company Rosneft, retreating from what was one of its most promising investments until Western sanctions got in the way.

headline.main: Exxon Mobil Scraps a Russian Deal, Stymied by Sanctions
headline.print_headline: Thwarted by Sanctions, Exxon Scraps Russia Deal

docs.abstract: The company will increase its output of oil and natural gas in the Permian Basin of West Texas and New Mexico to 600,000 barrels a day by 2025.
docs.snippet: The company will increase its output of oil and natural gas in the Permian Basin of West Texas and New Mexico to 600,000 barrels a day by 2025.
docs.lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — Exxon Mobil announced on Tuesday that it would triple its oil and gas production in the nation’s hottest shale field by 2025 in the newest sign that the boom in national crude production is gaining momentum.

headline.main: Exxon Mobil Tripling Its Bet on the Hottest U.S. Shale Field
headline.print_headline: Exxon Mobil Plans to Triple Its Bet on Hottest Shale Field in U.S.

docs.abstract: The move was expected because the country’s state-owned oil company had fallen behind on paying its bills from companies that maintain and operate its oil and gas wells.

docs.lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — Halliburton, the global oil service company, announced on Monday that it had written off its remaining investment of $312 million in Venezuela, as oil production in the politically polarized and virtually bankrupt country continues to plummet.

headline.main: Halliburton Writes Off Remaining $312 Million Invested in Venezuela
headline.print_headline: Halliburton Writes Off Investments In Venezuela

docs.abstract: Domestic demand continues to fall as coal is displaced by natural gas in power plants. The impact is being felt at a Pennsylvania mine about to close.
docs.snippet: Domestic demand continues to fall as coal is displaced by natural gas in power plants. The impact is being felt at a Pennsylvania mine about to close.
docs.lead_paragraph: BOBTOWN, Pa. — When Nic Zmija applied for a job at the 4 West coal mine three years ago, he was tantalized by a fat raise and a secure future. Once hired, he was told that someday even his two young sons had jobs waiting for them.

headline.main: Coal’s Decline Seems Impervious to Trump’s Promises

docs.abstract: The gap between short- and long-term interest rates has shrunk, and if the trend intensifies, it may be a classic harbinger of recession.
